text.section:
In a proceeding for a violation under this part:
the State has the burden to prove the guilt of the defendant to the same extent as is required by law in the trial of a criminal case;
the court shall apply the evidentiary standards as prescribed by law for the trial of a criminal case;
the court shall ensure that the defendant has received a copy of the charges against the defendant and that the defendant understands those charges;
the defendant is entitled to:
cross-examine each witness who appears against the defendant;
produce evidence and witnesses on the defendant's own behalf;
testify on the defendant's own behalf if the defendant chooses to do so; and
be represented by counsel of the defendant's own selection and expense;
the defendant may enter a plea of guilty or not guilty;
the verdict shall be:
guilty of a civil violation; or
not guilty of a civil violation; and
before entering a judgment, a court may place the defendant on probation in the same manner and to the same extent as is permitted by law in a criminal case.
